+### User Features
+-   **Multi-Format Support**: Load `.glb`, `.gltf`, `.fbx`, `.obj`, and more via drag & drop or from a URL.
+-   **Interactive Controls**: Orbit, zoom, and pan the camera with smooth, damped controls.
+-   **Scene Customization**: Adjust lighting, change the background (color, gradient, or HDRI), and toggle a grid.
+-   **Effects**: Enable a post-processing "Bloom" effect for a glow effect on bright materials.
+-   **Screenshot**: Capture the current view as a PNG image.
+-   **Animation Support**: Play, pause, and reset embedded animations in glTF models.

----
+### Developer Features
+-   **Zero-Build Setup**: Runs directly in the browser with no `npm` installation or build step required.
+-   **Vanilla JavaScript**: Written in plain ES6 JavaScript with no framework dependencies.
+-   **CDN-Powered**: All `three.js` dependencies are loaded from a public CDN.
+
+## Quick Start
+
+1.  Clone or download this repository.
+2.  Open the `index.html` file in a modern web browser.
+3.  Load a model using the controls in the sidebar.
+
+## Deployment
+
+This project can be deployed to any static web hosting service.
+
+### GitHub Pages (Recommended)
+1.  **Fork this repository.**
+2.  In your forked repository, go to **Settings > Pages**.
+3.  Under "Build and deployment," select **Deploy from a branch**.
+4.  Choose the `main` branch and the `/ (root)` folder, then click **Save**.
+5.  Your viewer will be live at `https://your-username.github.io/3d_modelview/` within a few minutes.
+
+## Development
+
+This project is in an early stage and has a very simple architecture.
+
+-   **Core Logic**: All application code is in `script.js`.
+-   **Dependencies**: All `three.js` libraries are loaded from a CDN, as defined in `index.html`. There is no `package.json` or `node_modules` folder.
+
+### Project Roadmap
+
+This project is currently undergoing improvements. The immediate goals are:
+1.  **[Refactor Monolithic Script](https://github.com/melbinjp/3d_modelview/issues/1)**: Break down `script.js` into smaller, more manageable ES6 modules.
+2.  **[Introduce a Build System](https://github.com/melbinjp/3d_modelview/issues/1)**: Add Vite to manage dependencies from npm, enable modern tooling, and bundle the application.
+3.  **[Add Automated Tests](https://github.com/melbinjp/3d_modelview/issues/2)**: Implement a testing suite with Vitest and Playwright to ensure code quality and prevent regressions.
+
+Contributions are welcome! Please see the open issues for areas where you can help.
